Sentencas: The perovskite oxide Ba0.5Sr0.5(Co0.8Fe0.2)0.8Mo0.2O3-delta (BSCFM) is used as both an anode and cathode in symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells (SSOFCs) because of its high electrocatalytic activity for both oxygen reduction reaction and fuel oxidation.
Titulo: Mo-doped Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-? as a high-performance symmetric electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Doping with Molybdenum (Mo) not only stabilizes the structure of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSCF) to improve the redox stability, it also dramatically enhances its electrochemical performance and thermal expansion compatibility.
Titulo: Mo-doped Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-? as a high-performance symmetric electrode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, the area specific polarization resistance (ASRp) for the BSCFM symmetric cell with La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) electrolyte is 0.064 omega cm2 and the maximum power density can reach 1225 mW cm-2 with wet H2 (3 % H2O) as fuel.
Titulo: Mo-doped Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-? as a high-performance symmetric electrode for solid oxide fuel cells
